If you use `Tristan-MP v2` for work/research presented in a publication (whether directly, or as a dependency to another package), we recommend and encourage the following acknowledgment:

  This research made use of "Tristan-MP v2" particle-in-cell code.

You may also use the following `bibtex` entry:

```
@software{hayk_hakobyan_2023_7566725,
  author       = {Hayk Hakobyan and
                  Anatoly Spitkovsky and
                  Alexander Chernoglazov and
                  Sasha Philippov and
                  Daniel Groselj and
                  Jens Mahlmann},
  title        = {PrincetonUniversity/tristan-mp-v2: v2.6},
  month        = jan,
  year         = 2023,
  publisher    = {Zenodo},
  version      = {v2.6},
  doi          = {10.5281/zenodo.7566725},
  url          = {https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7566725}
}
```

We also recommend to link to the source code on github: https://github.com/PrincetonUniversity/tristan-mp-v2.
